%N A392754 a(n) = the smallest value k such that A381466(k) = n or -1 if no such k exists.
%C A392754 A particular value k must appear in A381466 at or before index 6*k^2 - 2*k. If such a k doesn't appear in A381466 by then, a(k) = -1.
%H A392754 Sam Chapman, <a href="/A392754/b392754.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2000</a>
%e A392754 The first time A381466(k) = 3 is when k = 12, so a(3) = 12.
%e A392754 A381466(k) is greater than 1 for all k, so a(1) = -1.
